data.meta_description: Jul 2, 2020 - Judy Garland (born Frances Ethel Gumm; June 10, 1922 â€“ June 22, 1969) was an American actress, singer, dancer, and vaudevillian. During a career that spanned 45 years, she attained international stardom as an actress in both musical and dramatic roles, as a recording artist, and on the concert stage. Respected for her versatility, she received a Juvenile Academy Award, a Golden Globe Award, and a Special Tony Award.  In 1962 Garland won the Grammy Award for Album of the Year.
